We recommend that the Municipal Government enhance its compliance with policies and procedures on Local Roads Asset Management System by:
Requiring the submission of the report of the Local Road Network by the GSO/Municipal Treasurer in order to implement and monitor the recognition of the account Local Road Network in the books of accounts;

Improving the maintenance of subsidiary ledger for the Road and it components;

Making proper disclosure in the Financial Statement of Road Network System;

Exercising proper reconciliation between Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network and Local Road Network Ledger Card and make the necessary adjustment;

Providing cost to specific Road Network in order to have proper valuation and completeness of the Road Network Account.

It is recommended that the municipality’s GAD Focal Point System shall conduct gender mainstreaming through gender audit and gender analysis of its policies, programs, services and the current situation of the municipality in terms of GAD compliance;
To equip the GFPS with the in-depth knowledge and capacity on GAD, it also recommended that they shall undergo trainings and seminars such as those relating to gender-responsive planning and budgeting, gender analysis, gender audit and the use of various GAD tools for the LGU’s GAD implementation of PAPs; and
Revisit and strictly comply with the provisions of Republic Act No. 9710 and other provisions of law.

We recommend that the Municipality enhance its compliance with policies and procedures in:

Completing the actual physical count and the RPCPPE and reconcile the established differences to have accurate Fixed Asset records and reports for the Municipality for which it is held accountable and provide adequate disclosures to guide the users of information;

Maintaining proper Fixed Asset records for all Municipality’s fixed assets; 

Assigning Fixed Asset to end user or the least the head of office having custody of the assets to facilitate easy monitoring for inventory purposes and ensure that the same are being kept and safeguarded by responsible personnel 

Updating information in the Fixed Asset records;

Coordinating with different personnel/offices of the Municipality in order to gather information as to the amount of acquisition cost and the date of acquisition to be able to recognized depreciation expense.

If no information is available, since in the actual physical count of these assets they are classified as serviceable, proper appraisal on the remaining useful life of the asset should be done and the corresponding depreciation expense shall be computed based on the  book – value as presented in the financial statements.

Disposing unserviceable properties.
